   "source": [
    "## Overview of the Unrecognized Population\n",
    "\n",
    "The `{python} f\"{unrecog:,}\"` rows that Step 5 could not resolve fall into three buckets, each\n",
    "requiring a different strategy:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Root cause | Rows | Strategy |\n",
    "|------------|-----:|----------|\n",
    "| No / zero purchase history | `{python} f\"{len(no_ph):,}\"` | External enrichment (agentic search **or** catalogue match) |\n",
    "| Very low purchase history (1–4 units) | `{python} f\"{len(low_ph):,}\"` | Similar-product transfer + analyst review |\n",
    "| Some history but price out of range | `{python} f\"{len(some_ph):,}\"` | Threshold relaxation / cluster expansion |\n",
    "\n",
    ": {.striped .hover}\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Solution A — Agentic Web Search for Zero-History Products\n",
    "\n",
    "### The problem\n",
    "\n",
    "When a product has **no purchase history at all**, Step 5 has no anchors to compute\n",
    "proximity against — no DBSCAN cluster, no WAP, nothing.  The only signal available is\n",
    "the product description itself.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Proposed approach\n",
    "\n",
    "An agentic pipeline can augment these rows autonomously:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Query construction** — from `RecognizedProductDesc`, `RecognizedManufacturerName`,\n",
    "   and `RecognizedProductCatalogNumber` build a structured search query\n",
    "   (e.g., `\"Abbott 1192ANS Anchor SwiftLock unit of measure\"` or a medical-device pricing\n",
    "   database lookup).\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Search & parse** — the agent calls a web search tool or a medical product catalogue\n",
    "   API and extracts candidate UOM labels and typical pack sizes.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Citation attachment** — every suggestion is stored with its source URL and snippet\n",
    "   so an analyst can verify it before accepting.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Confidence flagging** — the agent rates its own confidence (e.g., \"found exact\n",
    "   catalog number\" vs. \"matched by description keyword\").  Low-confidence suggestions are\n",
    "   flagged for mandatory human review before write-back.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What needs to be built and tested\n",
    "\n",
    "- Prompt engineering to reliably extract structured UOM data from unstructured web pages.\n",
    "- A de-duplication pass to collapse near-identical suggestions.\n",
    "- A review UI that surfaces the citation alongside the suggested UOM for analyst sign-off.\n",
    "- A feedback loop: accepted suggestions are written back into the purchase history so future\n",
    "  runs can resolve the same products without another search.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Trade-offs\n",
    "\n",
    "| Benefit | Risk |\n",
    "|---------|------|\n",
    "| Extends coverage to truly novel products | Hallucination / incorrect web data — must require analyst approval |\n",
    "| Provides auditable citations | Adds latency and API cost per zero-history product |\n",
    "| Self-improving over time as accepted results grow history | Needs prompt fine-tuning per product category |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Solution B — Similar-Product Transfer (Purchase History Bridge)\n",
    "\n",
    "### The problem\n",
    "\n",
    "The `{python} f\"{len(low_ph):,}\"` rows with very low purchase history have *some* data but not\n",
    "enough to build a reliable DBSCAN cluster or meaningful WAP.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Proposed approach\n",
    "\n",
    "Rather than going to the web, look inside the existing purchase history for **similar\n",
    "products**:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Similarity candidates** — for a product with sparse history, find other products\n",
    "   in the catalogue that share:\n",
    "   - Same `RecognizedManufacturerID`\n",
    "   - Same `RecognizedProductTypeID`\n",
    "   - Similar description tokens (keyword overlap or embedding distance)\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **UOM profile transfer** — the similar product's ThresholdV2 clusters and WAP are\n",
    "   borrowed as a *prior*.  The proximity scoring in Step 5 runs exactly as normal, just\n",
    "   with the borrowed thresholds substituting for the absent ones.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Downgraded confidence** — because the thresholds are borrowed, the resulting\n",
    "   confidence score is multiplied by a transfer discount factor (e.g., 0.80) to signal\n",
    "   to downstream consumers that this is an inferred — not directly observed — assignment.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Analyst review trigger** — rows resolved via transfer are surfaced in a separate\n",
    "   review queue so analysts can confirm the analogy is valid for that product category.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What needs to be discussed with analysts\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Acceptable similarity criteria** — does same manufacturer + same product type\n",
    "  constitute a strong enough analogy?  Are there categories where this would be\n",
    "  systematically misleading (e.g., two products with the same type ID but very different\n",
    "  pricing tiers)?\n",
    "- **Discount factor calibration** — how much should transferred confidence be penalised?\n",
    "- **Segment sensitivity** — certain clinical categories (e.g., implants vs. consumables)\n",
    "  may require different similarity rules.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Trade-offs\n",
    "\n",
    "| Benefit | Risk |\n",
    "|---------|------|\n",
    "| Uses existing, trusted purchase data — no external calls | Wrong analogy can propagate a systematic error |\n",
    "| Fast — no added latency | Similarity is hard to define without analyst input |\n",
    "| Gracefully degrades to unrecognized if no similar product found | Requires a new similarity index to be maintained |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Solution C — Threshold Relaxation for Out-of-Range Prices\n",
    "\n",
    "### The problem\n",
    "\n",
    "The `{python} f\"{len(some_ph):,}\"` rows with adequate history fail because their file `PriceUOM`\n",
    "falls outside *every* DBSCAN cluster at a distance where the proximity score is below 0.30.\n",
    "\n",
    "Common causes:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Supplier price change** — the vendor raised or lowered prices since the last purchase,\n",
    "  shifting the quote outside the historical band.\n",
    "- **New pack size** — the supplier is now selling in a quantity not previously ordered\n",
    "  (e.g., BX/24 when history only has BX/12 and BX/100).\n",
    "- **Currency / unit mismatch** — a price-per-case was accidentally quoted as price-per-each.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Proposed approaches\n",
    "\n",
    "#### C1 — Widened acceptance window (lower LOG_EPS threshold)\n",
    "\n",
    "`LOG_EPS = 0.25` currently corresponds to a roughly 1.8× tolerance from the cluster edge.\n",
    "Increasing it to `0.40` extends tolerance to ~2.5×.  This is a global change and must be\n",
    "evaluated on a hold-out set to measure false-positive impact.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### C2 — Price-trend adjustment\n",
    "\n",
    "For products with a time-stamped purchase history, the system can detect upward or downward\n",
    "price trends and project the cluster range forward.  A product whose EA price has trended\n",
    "from $10 → $13 → $16 over 12 months is likely priced around $19 today; the cluster built\n",
    "on 12-month-old data will be offset.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### C3 — Analyst escalation queue\n",
    "\n",
    "Rows where the best candidate score is 0.20–0.30 (just below acceptance) are surfaced\n",
    "in a dedicated review queue.  The analyst sees the best DBSCAN candidate, its score, and\n",
    "the distance from the cluster edge — making a quick accept/reject decision fast.  Accepted\n",
    "overrides are recorded and used to retrain the threshold or expand the cluster.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Prioritisation Matrix"
   ]
  },
